modules.description: Registers an application with the Windows event log and reports events with specific types, categories, event IDs, and insertion strings. It works with event log handles, event types, and string arrays to record structured log entries. Used to log application-specific events with detailed metadata for system monitoring and diagnostics.

Provides a function to create a log reporter that writes entries to the Windows event log, using specified category and event IDs. Works with the Eventlog.t type and integer values for categorization. Used to integrate application logging with system-level event tracking for diagnostics and monitoring.

Provides functions to write entries to the Windows event log, including error, warning, and information levels. Operates on strings for message content and integers for event identifiers. Used to integrate application diagnostics directly into the system's event monitoring infrastructure.

Constructs a logging reporter that writes entries to the Windows event log, allowing specification of category and event IDs. Works with the Win_eventlog.Eventlog.t type and integer-based event identifiers. Used to integrate application logs with system-level event tracking for monitoring and diagnostics.

Records application events to the Windows event log using structured metadata such as event types, categories, and insertion strings. It supports creating log reporters that associate entries with specific categories and event IDs, enabling detailed system diagnostics. Operations include registering events, managing log handles, and inserting custom strings for contextual information. This allows for precise logging of application behavior, facilitating real-time monitoring and error tracking.

Registers event sources and reports events to a log, using a specified server or the local log. It operates on a log handle type and event type identifiers, supporting event categorization and localized message insertion. Used for logging application-specific events with structured metadata and dynamic message parameters.
